The paper discusses the design of an LSTM accelerator for energy-constrained devices, which falls under the categories of embedded systems (cs.ET) and energy-efficient computing (cs.EM). The use of neural networks and artificial intelligence technology also places it under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the architectural innovations and performance optimization techniques used in the design, which falls under the category of computer architecture (cs.AR). Finally, the use of the accelerator in real-time applications and embedded systems suggests that it may also fall under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
